# Echo Stealthwalker
>War Master

Echo was a sleek ice-blue [[Races/Dragon\|dragon]], bonded to [[Characters/Indigo Shadeslayer\|Indigo Shadeslayer]]. He was notably the first dragon to form a bond with a [[Races/Dragon Rider\|Rider]] since the departure of [[Characters/Eragon II\|Eragon II]] to the east, and he helped his Rider form the [[Groups/New Rider Order\|New Rider Order]]. Together, they traveled Alagaësia searching for new Rider candidates and rebuilt [[Locations/Doru Araeba\|Doru Araeba]] to be their stronghold once more. 

Before his body-death, he was one of (if not *the*) Riders' greatest fighters. He has a vast array of combat knowledge and experience, and he used to be the primarily combat master for the dragons and Riders of the [[Groups/New Rider Order\|Order]]. Since [[Characters/Bastille Soulkeeper\|Bastille Soulkeeper]] has brought his [[Library/Eldunarí\|Eldunarí]] back to [[Locations/Doru Araeba\|Doru Araeba]], he has not resumed that role, claiming that his days as instructor are over. 

He is currently 398, and was 363 when his body was lost. Some question why Bastille was entrusted with his [[Library/Eldunarí\|Eldunarí]], given the fact that it was [[Characters/Raegal Darkstar\|Raegal Darkstar]] who killed his Rider, but if Echo has ever given an answer it is not one that has been shared.
